COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 11:09AM PT today, over 1.3 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 24.5 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.5 thousand new infections have been reported and 12 deaths. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 14.8 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. Of those 16 years and older, 42.6% have their 1st shot and 3.7% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 2.3 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~7 days for new deliveries to get into arms. At the current rate of 249 thousand doses per day, all adult Canadians should have the first dose by Jul-29 and fully vaccinated by Nov-25. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 15 or younger.
